sent:
Examples of adaptations include the following :

Changing the physical environment : providing handrails for walking

Changing the rules : providing a buddy in a relay race

Changing the conventional way an activity is performed : placing toothpaste in the palm , then on the brush rather than squeezing toothpaste onto the brush

Changing the routine sequence : brushing teeth while bathing

Reducing the complexity of a task or the response alternatives : choosing between 2 items for snack rather than 5 items ; paying with dollar bills only ( cost-plus-one strategy ) rather than coins

Providing adaptive devices or cues : using placemat guides that include high-contrast pictures for setting a table

Highlighting relevant stimuli : placing a brightly-colored tactile marker on the on-off button of a tape recorder

Using personal assistance : having a classmate open a locker with a key ( Chen &; Dote-Kwan , 1995 ; Holowach , 1989 ) .
